# OpenRouter API key for development / local use.
# 
# INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to configs/openrouter.key (or OPENROUTER_API_KEY.txt)
# 2. Paste your real key on the first line only (no extra spaces/newlines).
# 3. The file is gitignored (see .gitignore).
#
# PREFERRED METHOD (all environments including prod/CI):
#   Set the environment variable OPENROUTER_API_KEY instead.
#   Example (PowerShell): $env:OPENROUTER_API_KEY = "sk-or-..."
#   Example (bash): export OPENROUTER_API_KEY="sk-or-..."
#
# SECURITY:
# - Never commit real keys to git.
# - For production, use proper secret management (env vars injected at runtime,
#   Kubernetes secrets, AWS Secrets Manager, etc.). File-based keys are for
#   local developer convenience only.
# - The application will log a warning if it loads a key from a file.

sk-or-REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_KEY_HERE
